hooks/pcmk.py.message:
This function has very awkward return value: Dict[Any, Union[Any, List[Any]]

The issue is that now the caller of the function has to work out for each value whether it is a list or not when using the value; i.e. it's just pushed the issue of working this out to the caller of the function.

It would be better if the the function returned a known value type after the merge (e.g. List) EVEN if there is only one element, and then the caller can just take the first value from the list as needed.

This makes it easier to use this function.  In this case it would make the code easier as in:

    results = {k: [v] for k,v in dictionaries[0].items()}
    for dictionary in dictionaries[1:]:
        for k, v in dictionary.items():
            try:
                results[k].append(v)
            except KeyError:
                results[k] = [v]

    return results

Obviously, this doesn't throw an assertion error; you could add that back in as required.

